                        p 
                            strong.text-red PR: 
                            |  I use painters more for content than for the quality of the paint. I never used the world “painterly” in my book. I’m not talking about that, I’m talking about the design aspect, the way Vasari talked about it. It’s in the very first sentence of the book. What Vasari said was absolutely what I was talking about, too.

