                            strong.text-red PR: 
                            |  Well, this is the vocabulary of art, the vocabulary of form. In the Leger problem I give to students I went to the trouble of examining the things that I thought Leger contributed, and I actually broke it down. It’s in my book. The assignment has been done by Harvard and a couple of other schools. That’s the idea, it’s the way one learns. Leger was another original. He was an architect. He liked a compass and ruler and straight edge. But he also had a terrific sense of humor. Most of these things are very funny. Look at that kid, 
